    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Proverbs",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 18,
        "summary": "A fool's mouth is his destruction\u2014Whoever obtains a wife obtains a good thing\u2014A man who has friends must show himself friendly.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Through desire a man, having separated himself, seeketh and intermeddleth with all wisdom.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 56,
                        "end": 59
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A fool hath no delight in understanding, but that his heart may discover itself.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "When the wicked cometh, then cometh also contempt, and with ignominy reproach.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 28
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The words of a man's mouth are as deep waters, and the wellspring of wisdom as a flowing brook.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 20:5.",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 45
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 33
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 47,
                        "end": 50
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 76,
                        "end": 78
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "It is not good to accept the person of the wicked, to overthrow the righteous in judgment.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 82:2.",
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 35
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 5
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A fool's lips enter into contention, and his mouth calleth for strokes.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Contention.",
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 35
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "A fool's mouth is his destruction, and his lips are the snare of his soul.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 10:14.",
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 14
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 64:8.",
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 33
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 17
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 51
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The words of a talebearer are as wounds, and they go down into the innermost parts of the belly.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0slanderer. TG\u00a0Gossip; Honesty.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 25
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 29
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He also that is slothful in his work is brother to him that is a great waster.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Laziness.",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Waste.",
                        "start": 71,
                        "end": 77
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The name of the Lord is a strong tower: the righteous runneth into it, and is safe.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Sam. 22:3; Ps. 61:3.",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 38
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 23
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The rich man's wealth is his strong city, and as an high wall in his own conceit.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 19:24 (16\u201324).",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 8
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 10:15.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 21
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 24
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Before destruction the heart of man is haughty, and before honour is humility.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 29:23.",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 46
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 7:23 (23\u201324); D&C 112:10.",
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 77
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 66,
                        "end": 68
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He that answereth a matter before he heareth it, it is folly and shame unto him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Rashness.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 17
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 45,
                        "end": 48
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 54
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The spirit of a man will sustain his infirmity; but a wounded spirit who can bear?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The heart of the prudent getteth knowledge; and the ear of the wise seeketh knowledge.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Prudence.",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Knowledge.",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 42
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "A man's gift maketh room for him, and bringeth him before great men.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "He that is first in his own cause seemeth just; but his neighbour cometh and searcheth him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mark 9:35.",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 16
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 10
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 41
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The lot causeth contentions to cease, and parteth between the mighty.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 16:33.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 7
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "A brother offended is harder to be won than a strong city: and their contentions are like the bars of a castle.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Brotherhood and Sisterhood.",
                        "start": 2,
                        "end": 9
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Offense.",
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 18
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Contention.",
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 80
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 38
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 63,
                        "end": 68
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 81,
                        "end": 84
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A man's belly shall be satisfied with the fruit of his mouth; and with the increase of his lips shall he be filled.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 65
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Death and life are in the power of the tongue: and they that love it shall eat the fruit thereof.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 12:37 (34\u201337); Alma 12:14.",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 45
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 18
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Whoso findeth a wife findeth a good thing, and obtaineth favour of the Lord.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Marriage, Wives.",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 20
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 5
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 42
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The poor useth entreaties; but the rich answereth roughly.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 19:7.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 8
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 32:5 (1\u20135).",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 25
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "A man that hath friends must shew himself friendly: and there is a friend that sticketh closer than a brother.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 27:10. TG\u00a0Friendship.",
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 73
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Brotherhood and Sisterhood.",
                        "start": 102,
                        "end": 109
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 6,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 74,
                        "end": 78
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}